 The addressed topics include a course of introduction to optical/IR interferometry covering the history and basic principles, a course on diffraction-dominated observational astronomy, and a course presenting the principles and instrumentation of optical long baseline interferometry. This book will be a valuable reference for researchers and students in the coming years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAstronomyvObservationsvCongresses. 0aImaging systems in astronomyvCongresses. 0aInterferometryvCongresses. 0aOptics, AdaptivevCongresses. 0aResolution (Optics)vCongresses. 0aTelescopesvCongresses. 4aAstrophysics. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Astrophysics.2bisacsh1 aLagadec, Eric, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLebreton, Yveline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEDP Sciences Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2020z978311075640140uhttps://doi.org/10.1051/978-2-7598-2373-440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759823734423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9782759823734.jpg  a978-3-11-075640-1  EDP Sciences Contemporary eBook-Package 2016-2020c2016d2020  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK